\int \dfrac{9x^2+13x-6}{(x-1)(x+1)^2} dx
(A+B) x^2 + (2A+C)x +(A-B-C) = 9x^2+13 x -6
A,B,C
x
A+B=9
2A+C = 13
A-B-C = -6
\frac{5}{x+1}+\frac{5}{(x+1)^2}+\frac{4}{x-1} = \frac{9x^2+13x-6}{(x-1)(x+1)^2}
\dfrac{9x^2 + 13x - 6}{(x-1)(x+1)^2}
4C = 16 \implies C = 4
A=B=5
\dfrac{A}{(x+1)^2} + \dfrac{B}{x+1} + \dfrac{C}{x-1}
B+C = 9\\ 2C+A = 13\\ C - A - B = -6
\dfrac{9x^2 + 13x - 6}{(x-1)(x+1)^2} = \dfrac5{(x+1)^2} + \dfrac5{x+1} + \dfrac4{x-1}
